<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF90BA3CB6E4F479B109FBB8" pageId="44" pageNumber="663" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF90BA3CB6E4F479B109FBB8" blockId="44.[757,1352,635,1062]" lastBlockId="44.[145,1356,1069,2366]" pageId="44" pageNumber="663">
In 1816, L.. Oken named this species 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF90BA3CB0EBF479B1F3FCAF" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Myopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="663" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="senegalensis">Myopterus senegalensis</taxonomicName>
but the name was shown to be invalid by J. E. Hill in 1969. As the original syntypes were lost, Adam and coworkers designated a neoholotype and four neoparatypes, from 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFF90BA3CB001F4BEB6A4FC31" box="[1043,1154,990,1023]" name="Senegal" pageId="44" pageNumber="663">Senegal</collectingCountry>
, in 1993. The form albatus was recognized as a subspecies by K. F. Koopman in 1989, Adam and colleagues in 1993, N. B. Simmons in 2005, and J. Fahr in 2013. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
